Observation Details: Two birds travelling together, calling back and forth. First seen in forest bordering meadow of goldenrod, off Hank's Trail. Single bird seen later, in overgrown hedgerow along "Farm Road" (other side of meadow), may have been one of earlier two birds.

Reliable in this spot every early Fall and findable if I put in the effort and get the timing right. Bird stayed in and foraged in thicket; photo impossible. Partially obscured views of active bird showed unmarked tripartite coloring: olive on dorsal, darker full hood blending to conspicuous dull yellow undersides. Illusion of long body and short tail (extended undertail coverts). Decent audio of chip notes despite prominent Eastern chipmunk.
Flushed practically from between my legs into the corn patch. Adult male.

FOY. northern hedgerow in orchard, adjacent to pumpkin patch overgrown with mugwort. heard blackpoll-like ‘zeep’ flight call then it popped up for 15 seconds and called a few times before diving back into brushy hedgerow. exactly the same spot where one hung out for several days in mid-September 2016.
